This paper is about improving response selection in retrieval-based chatbots using pre-trained contextualized representations. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a dialogue generation model, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The proposed method also involves blending contextualized representations at different levels, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning and neural networks, and thus falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which are covered in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural network architecture design, which is covered in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
